🚨 CrowdStrike has had its NPM packages compromised
𝘔𝘺 𝘣𝘪𝘨 '𝘏𝘈𝘊𝘒𝘌𝘋' 𝘴𝘵𝘢𝘮𝘱 𝘪𝘴 𝘣𝘢𝘤𝘬. 
Crowdstrike has been caught in a Supply chain attack that so far includes 180 packages from various organizations. 

𝗖𝗿𝗼𝘄𝗱𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗶𝗸𝗲 𝗽𝗮𝗰𝗸𝗮𝗴𝗲𝘀 𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗺𝗶𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗶𝗻𝗰𝗹𝘂𝗱𝗲 
@crowdstrike/commitlint
@crowdstrike/falcon-shoelace
@crowdstrike/foundry-js
@crowdstrike/glide-core
@crowdstrike/logscale-dashboard
@crowdstrike/logscale-file-editor
@crowdstrike/logscale-parser-edit
@crowdstrike/logscale-search
@crowdstrike/tailwind-toucan-base

This appears to be a continuation of the Tinycolor attack first discovered by Daniel Pereira that Socket and StepSecurity had reported on. Both discovered that a combined 40 packages were compromised. Since then, an additional 140 packages have been compromised, including those from Crowdstrike. This is ongoing, so expect more compromises to follow. 

